  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "Security update for apache-commons-compress",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "Summary"
    },
    {
      "Text": "This update for apache-commons-compress fixes the following issues:\n\n- Updated to 1.21\n- CVE-2021-35515: Fixed an infinite loop when reading a specially crafted 7Z archive. (bsc#1188463)\n- CVE-2021-35516: Fixed an excessive memory allocation when reading a specially crafted 7Z archive. (bsc#1188464)\n- CVE-2021-35517: Fixed an excessive memory allocation when reading a specially crafted TAR archive. (bsc#1188465)\n- CVE-2021-36090: Fixed an excessive memory allocation when reading a specially crafted ZIP archive. (bsc#1188466)\n",
      "Title": "Details",
      "Type": "General"
    },
